989
01:31:54,308 --> 01:32:00,514
Uh, I, I definitely echo everything Mr. Starella just said, uh, in, in spades.

990
01:32:01,114 --> 01:32:07,099
I just want to echo a few things from what, uh, counselor marks was, was talking about.

991
01:32:07,399 --> 01:32:10,882
Uh, he's mentioned one street that hasn't been done in six decades.

992
01:32:10,962 --> 01:32:12,103
That's, that's my street.

993
01:32:12,224 --> 01:32:12,744
Evan street.

994
01:32:12,844 --> 01:32:15,326
I've been before the city council before, uh,

995
01:32:18,412 --> 01:32:21,812
And it's a very sad commentary on the city of Medford.

996
01:32:22,175 --> 01:32:40,330
to see a budget of $167 million when residents on my street, Mr. President, were told by at least two counselors that the repairs that were in dire need, critical condition, were going to be done this May.

997
01:32:41,030 --> 01:32:48,236
I came to the city hall and I spoke to the engineer who told me all the red tape it has to go through.

998
01:32:48,696 --> 01:32:49,676
about a contract.

999
01:32:50,496 --> 01:33:04,960
A neighbor of mine told me yesterday that upon speaking to somebody in City Hall, I won't mention any names, said that contract is now having problems, so it doesn't look like our street's gonna be done this year.

1000
01:33:06,300 --> 01:33:15,662
After being told by several people that it was gonna be done, the residents of Evans Street are outraged.

1001
01:33:16,384 --> 01:33:44,403
Mr. President, when we're paying two income taxes, excise taxes, property taxes that go up every year, a new connectivity fee coming at us in the water tax account that has a surplus in it, to see a $167 million budget that's about to be approved, as Mr. Starewa said, that 80% of it is going towards salaries and the infrastructure repairs not being done,

1002
01:33:45,739 --> 01:33:47,520
It will be reflected on this body.

1003
01:33:48,880 --> 01:33:52,861
It's a primary reason why I am running for city council this year.

1004
01:33:52,901 --> 01:33:54,182
This is not a campaign speech.

1005
01:33:54,242 --> 01:33:57,383
I know, but I can announce that I'm a candidate, Mr. President.

1006
01:33:57,703 --> 01:33:58,103
I can.

1007
01:33:58,123 --> 01:33:59,684
If that threatens you, good.

1008
01:34:00,744 --> 01:34:00,944
Good.

1009
01:34:01,772 --> 01:34:05,257
Because we need new voices on the city council, Mr. President.

1010
01:34:05,317 --> 01:34:11,466
We need new people that are going to come in here and have the political will to finally stand up and say no.

1011
01:34:11,646 --> 01:34:13,048
This is not a political step.

1012
01:34:13,208 --> 01:34:14,671
I know that, Mr. President.

1013
01:34:14,711 --> 01:34:15,932
Thank you for reminding me that.

1014
01:34:15,952 --> 01:34:16,593
Thank you.

1015
01:34:21,400 --> 01:34:31,628
The reinvestment in the arts that Councillor Marks spoke to is a stabilizing tax base, especially with that Chevalier Theatre.

1016
01:34:31,748 --> 01:34:34,951
That's only going to get $97,000 this year under this budget.

1017
01:34:35,171 --> 01:34:35,832
It's outrageous.

1018
01:34:36,292 --> 01:34:45,699
It's outrageous, especially when this downtown business district is suffering so much for the extended repair of the Craddock Bridge that's now added another year, another $10 million to it.

1019
01:34:49,025 --> 01:35:00,267
Far too many residents of this community are at their wits end with vital repairs that are not being done and seeing a budget increase to $167 million.

1020
01:35:01,228 --> 01:35:14,010
I respectfully ask you to vote no on this budget until such a time that it reflects adequate responsibility for all the millions of millions of tax dollars that these residents are paying.

1021
01:35:14,290 --> 01:35:15,271
Thank you, Mr. President.

